summary: This is a search and seizure warrant issued by the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York authorizing the search of six binders containing CDs seized from suitcases on July 11, 2019. The warrant seeks evidence related to violations of sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy statutes, specifically looking for documents, communications, photographs, and other electronic data concerning victims.

persons.name: Kelly Maguire
persons.context: Special Agent who seized the binders with CDs from suitcases on or about July 11, 2019.

persons.name: Hon. L. Cott
persons.context: The magistrate judge who issued and signed the search and seizure warrant.

events.title: Seizure of binders and CDs
events.description: Special Agent Kelly Maguire seized two blue binders with CDs from a blue suitcase and three blue binders with various CDs plus one clear binder with a green spine with various CDs from a black suitcase.

keyFacts: The warrant authorizes search of six binders containing CDs seized from suitcases on July 11, 2019, for evidence of sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy.
The items were seized by Special Agent Kelly Maguire from two suitcases - a blue suitcase containing two binders and a black suitcase containing four binders.
The search targets evidence including documents/communications regarding victims, photographs of victims, nude/sexually suggestive photos of teenage girls or younger, and child erotica.
The warrant was issued by Magistrate Judge Hon. L. Cott in the Southern District of New York.
The investigation involves violations of 18 USC 1591 (Sex Trafficking of Minors) and 18 USC 371 (Sex Trafficking Conspiracy).
